## PHASE 0 — Foundations & safety (do FIRST; cheap insurance, unblocks all the rest)

**1. Staging + separate test DB** (was 5)
Learn how preview/staging works; stand up a Supabase **branch or second project** for testing
payments + new features so nothing is tested against live prod. *This unblocks safe testing of
every later item.* → ties to `6(left)…` A1. Deps: none. Effort: M.

**2. Deployment pipeline** (was 4)
Learn how to ship Next.js: Vercel vs Coolify vs your own app server; how the app code and API
routes deploy together (Next.js API routes deploy WITH the app — they're not a separate server);
preview deploys per branch; env-var management. Pick one host and document the deploy. Deps: none
(pairs with #1's previews). Effort: M.

**3. Production-grade code standard + dashboard refactor** (was 1)
Define what "production-grade" means here (file structure, naming, one-responsibility files,
typed hooks, no `any`, no dead code) and refactor the dashboard's worst offenders to match. Then
**every later feature follows this standard as you touch it** — don't rewrite everything up front.
Write a short `CONTRIBUTING`/onboarding doc. *Do this before #6–#11 so new code lands clean.*
Deps: none. Effort: L (ongoing).

> **+ Added 0a — Automated tests + CI gate.** Vitest (pure logic) + Playwright (5 flows) once #1
> exists; wire `tsc`+`lint`+`vitest` into GitHub Actions. Full plan already in `6(left)…` A2.
> **+ Added 0b — Observability.** Sentry (client+server) + a real log backend before launch, so
> prod failures are visible.

