## PHASE 2 — Revenue path (highest business value; this is what makes money)

**7. Storefront slug pages + payment + checkout + cart + wishlist** (was 7)
The buyer funnel end-to-end. The money plumbing (checkout→webhook→fulfillment→referral) is solid;
this is about the buyer UX + cart/wishlist completeness + the public slug pages. Deps: #1–#3.
Effort: L.

**8. The 4 editors (UI + features)** (was 6)
Link-in-bio / single-page / store / payment-link builders — the creators' core tool. Apply the
#3 standard. Deps: #3. Effort: L.

**9. Marketing surfaces** (was 8)
Public landing/pricing/blog/etc. working end-to-end; update the DB SaaS-style where features need
it (follow the "schema-in-sync" CLAUDE.md rule). Deps: #3. Effort: M.

